is usually considered non-monophyletic (e.g. see https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5664179/)

The Poder phylogeny goes something like:

(((((Beroida, Haeckeliidae),((Cestida,Thalassocalycida,Lobata), Pleurobrachiidae))),Platyctenida),Mertensiidae);


For the time being, to create the trichotomy (Cestida,Thalassocalycida,Lobata) we can simply take the OpenTree "Tentaculata" which includes
everything except the beroids, and remove the Platyctenida, Mertensiidae, Haeckeliidae, and Pleurobrachiidae i.e.

ott523271~-574291-1580-1583-747323

This is a horrible hack, but will have to do until a better Ctenophore coverage is obtained


